Each Target has the following properties:

**Properties**

**Description**

**All text to black**

Allows to enable the text to be in black on print.

**During text formatting**

Select one of the available options:

- **Optimize the page layout for optimal appearance (recommended): **predefin ed algorithm for text formatting; it process the layout of a whole paragraph at time to achieve the best aesthetically pleasant text distribution.

- **Optimize each line individually**: format each line of the paragraphs individually, the break points of the lines are not moved by inserting new text at the end of the paragraph as with the previous algorithm.

**Generate shapes using native instructions**

Creates graphics commands for generating shapes (such as rectangles) using

native instructions instead of drawing commands that depend on the spool format. This option is provided for compatibility with projects generated with previous version of the Designer. In new projects, it is enabled.

**Use advanced text spacing**

Allows to retain consecutive spaces in text blocks instead of compacting them. This option is provided for compatibility with projects generated with previous version of the Designer. In new projects, it is enabled.

**Insert additional breakpoints in tables**

Allows to insert page breaks in tables with nested bindings that would be kept together because of their relationship, avoiding an overflow on some documents

> Warning

If there are nested bindings in a table, the first data rows of the child bindings are automatically kept together to their parent to avoid a page break that separates them. If the data sequence contains a nesting with data rows at the lowest hierarchy level, the table layout may cause an overflow if this option is not set.

**Use tighter word and character spacing**

Allows to remove word and character spacing in rich text elements.

> Warning

This option should be used only when the spool size reduction is prioritized over speed production.

**Use part of application memory to process images faster**

Allows the application to use part of its runtime memory to process images faster.

> Warning

The application may need more memory to run depending on the images size.

**Country**

Indicates the regional settings to be used during print spool generation. These settings affect the low-level handling of values represented in different ways depending on the geographical area (e.g. dates, decimals, etc.). The default localization is Italy (IT).

Composer** parameters**

Group of additional settings to be sent to the module that performs the formatting. This information is often highly process-dependent.

> Note

In the Composer Options panel, the following options refer to the entire project and not to the single Target:

- Generate shapes using native instructions Use advanced text spacing

- Optimize the page layout for optimal appearance (recommended) Optimize each line individually

- Insert additional breakpoints in tables

- Use part of application memory to process images faster

- Their activation affects all the Targets configured in Output Management.

Composer is a web-based application for editing document templates which were created with Business Designer. It is used mainly to resolve dynamic fields into real data read from a database.
